This rule holds true, as a matter of fact, throughout Third Hand's play, even after the first trick. It helps your Partner to read your hand during the later play. In playing Third Hand high, then, you always select the bottom card of a sequence heading the led suit. Put another way, whenever you have cards of equal value so far as taking the trick is concerned, you lead the highest, but play the lowest. We will now explain this principle.|
